  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving pastoralist girls&apos; educational aspirations and attainment (Tanzania)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pastoralist communities in Tanzania face widespread discrimination, and their children, especially their girls, find it hard to get a decent education. Girls&apos;&apos; enrolment is lower than boys, drop-out rates are higher and they do not do as well academically. Many children are not taught by qualified teachers. Girls are particularly at risk of dropping out during the transition from primary to secondary school. This project aims to increase the numbers of pastoralist girls who make this transition successfully, and to improve their performance in school. A pre-form one school will be established, to give intensive English, Maths and local language lessons to pastoralist girls before they go to secondary school. By the end of the project, there will be more girls from pastoralist communities attending secondary school than ever before.</narrative>
  </description>
